<li><small><a href="/w/index.php?title=Albert_Vann_Fowler&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Albert Vann Fowler (page does not exist)">Albert Vann Fowler</a> (editor), <i>War and Civilization, Selections from A Study of History</i>, with a preface by Toynbee (New York, Oxford University Press 1950)</small></li>
<li><small>Introduction and translations, <i>Twelve Men of Action in Greco-Roman History</i> (Boston, Beacon Press 1952). Extracts from <a href="/wiki/Thucydides" title="Thucydides">Thucydides</a>, <a href="/wiki/Xenophon" title="Xenophon">Xenophon</a>, <a href="/wiki/Plutarch" title="Plutarch">Plutarch</a> and <a href="/wiki/Polybius" title="Polybius">Polybius</a>.</small></li>
